Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, no telling tales in my family. Oh no. I can very very - well remember going home one day, I must have been a very very tender age too, I must have been about si
x or seven. And - saying that so and so hit me. And I remember my father saying - and what did you do? Well, I said, he's bigger than me. He said, that doesn't matter. Go on, out you go. And always remember this my boy, if a boy hits you you hit him. It d
oesn't matter if you have a good hiding. And that always happened too. If he didn't tell me that my brothers would have done anyhow.
