\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4940319 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13846497\charrsid2252871 
Do you think she got a little bit of money from her side of the family which she then put towards the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5447395 SR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13846497\charrsid2252871 Oh no. Didn't get any money. No, the only money she
 ever had was made out of the shop. Oh no, my - my mother - was as poor as the - the Ratcliff's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4940319 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13846497\charrsid2252871 She didn't feel she was any different in social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5447395 SR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13846497\charrsid2252871 
Oh no. No, no. No, I would say it was just that - father - he had a full time job, he had a f
ull time job - looking after the clothing and boots and - maintaining the house and all that sort of thing - together with his own - other job, cleaning out the chapel and all that sort of thing, and - he didn't have time I suppose to worry about things. 
W
hich as I say they weren't all that important anyhow. But often my mother would refer to him - I know that I - if I got into very serious trouble - which I did, very often - that - she would always say to me - you wait 'til your father comes home, I'll te
ll him. And that to my mind was pretty awful. I - knew then that things had to happen. Because father wouldn't - look upon things so lightly. If I'd done wrong well I'd got to be punished, that's all there is about it.
\par 
